Date: Wed, 27 Feb 2008 19:26:33 -0800
From: 	akepner@sgi ...
Subject: [PATCH 3/3 v3] IB: expand ib_umem_get() prototype
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2008/2/27/536

Add a new parameter, dmasync, to the ib_umem_get() prototype. Use
dmasync = 1 when mapping user-allocated CQs with ib_umem_get().
Signed-off-by: Arthur Kepner <akepner@sgi.com>
---
